Sentencas: The corrosion behavior of three commercially available high chromium ferritic steels and one austenitic steel was tested in CO-containing simulated anode gas of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell.
Titulo: Behavior of Interconnect Steels in Carbon Containing Simulated Anode Gas of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Aim of the study was to evaluate the suitability of selected steels for interconnects in SOFC's with an operating temperature around 600 degrees C. Main emphasis was put on the effect of a nickel contact layer on the materials behavior in the high simulated anode gas.
Titulo: Behavior of Interconnect Steels in Carbon Containing Simulated Anode Gas of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In spite of the high carbon activity in the gas (a(C)>1) the steels in the as ground condition were found to form protective, chromium rich surface oxide scales and did not show indications for metal dusting or internal carburization, up to the maximum test times of 300 h. Presence of a metallic nickel layer resulted in carbon uptake of the steels, whereby the relative amounts increased with decreasing steel chromium content.
Titulo: Behavior of Interconnect Steels in Carbon Containing Simulated Anode Gas of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Interdiffusion between ferritic steel and nickel layer lead to austenite formation, with or without sigma-phase formation.
Titulo: Behavior of Interconnect Steels in Carbon Containing Simulated Anode Gas of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Diffusion of chromium into the nickel layer resulted in formation of a thin chromia based surface scale on the initial nickel coating.
Titulo: Behavior of Interconnect Steels in Carbon Containing Simulated Anode Gas of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This effect impedes the transfer of carbon from the gas into the nickel coated steel.
